                        "goal": "Goal 9. Industry, innovation and infrastructure",
                      
                        "priority": "Increased competitiveness of the region by increasing the research and innovation potential (Development of institutional potential for research and development, supporting cooperation between the research sector and the economy)",
                      
                        "definition": "The indicator determines the share of invention applications from a given voivodeship in the total number of inventions submitted to the Patent Office, expressed in %.",
                      
                        "unit": "percent",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "A reported invention (Patent application) is a solution to a specific problem of a technical nature, reported for protection to the appropriate office accepting the application, in order to obtain patent protection for a given invention.Source of definition: Act of 30 June 2000 - Industrial Property Law Place of publication: (Journal of Laws of 2023, item 1170).National procedure for reporting inventions for patenting (National procedure) - a procedure for all types of applications submitted directly to the patent office of a given country - from the territory of that country and from abroad under the Paris Convention of 1883.",
                      
